      <h2>After Closing</h2>

      <p>The work doesn't stop when you sign the last document:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Recording:</strong> The title company records the deed and mortgage with the county recorder's office ‚Äî typically within 24 hours</li>
        <li><strong>Disbursement:</strong> Funds are distributed to the seller, agents, lender, and other parties</li>
        <li><strong>Title policy:</strong> Your owner's title insurance policy is issued and mailed to you (usually within 2-4 weeks)</li>
        <li><strong>Keep your documents:</strong> Store your closing documents safely ‚Äî you'll need them for taxes and any future sale or refinance</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tips for a Smooth Closing</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Respond quickly</strong> to requests from your lender and title company</li>
        <li><strong>Don't make major financial changes</strong> between contract and closing (new credit cards, large purchases, job changes)</li>
        <li><strong>Keep funds traceable</strong> ‚Äî lenders need to verify the source of your down payment</li>
        <li><strong>Do a final walkthrough</strong> the day of or before closing</li>
        <li><strong>Ask questions early</strong> ‚Äî don't wait until closing day to raise concerns</li>
        <li><strong>Consider a <a href="/services/mobile-closings/">mobile closing</a></strong> for added convenience</li>
      </ul>

